Articles.Content:
**As most of you already know, Kerbal Space Program has partnered up with EUCL3D. Any awesome stock rocket or aircraft you have will be 3D printed in various sizes and ranging from $99-200 in price (So worth it)** ![:P](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif)**. However they look wickedly cool and I look forward to see Zeke's Full-Sized Shuttle 3D printed. So post your pictures of you 3D print to show how much of a fan you are for ksp.**

**You can go check out their website at:** [https://www.eucl3d.com/ksp](https://www.eucl3d.com/ksp)

![XQsEDLP.jpg](http://i.imgur.com/XQsEDLP.jpg)

Jeez, do they really start at $99? That's a lot of money...

Is it cheating to render a craft, overlay it into my hand and put it here? ![:P](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif)

I assume you can count that as a 3D print its fan work of your spacecraft but I think this still wins ![:P](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif)![ship3.0.0.jpg](https://cdn3.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4PmSHaIMgg-aRoPpWGDAhm8ldAc=/0x70:1000x633/640x360/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/45790498/ship3.0.0.jpg)

starting at 99 dollars lmao 

thats why theres the same 3 pics for 3d printed craftys

Ninety-nine dollars?

That's more expensive than the game itself!

Jeez, the least they can do is make them cheaper, I was looking forward to having one of my rockets on my desk but alas, it was not to be
